<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-559-155  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 559 155.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>LAN Times  Oct 22 1990 v7 n12 p107(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Tips on LAN Cabling system selection: cable can affect everythingfrom installation cost to insurance premiums. (tutorial)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Duncan, Thom.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Finding the correct cable for a particular network topology is anever-present challenge.andP;  The National Electronic Code controls themanner in which cables are installed in buildings.andP;  The code saysthat only fireproof cabling can be installed vertically in walls,in order to prevent the spread of fire.andP;  Twisted-pair calls fortwo sets of wire twisted together to prevent crosstalk.andP;  Telephonecable is twisted pair.andP;  Coaxial cable defines the common axisshared by shields, conductor and insulating material.andP;  A VCR cableis coaxial.andP;  A fiber-optic connection includes a digital or analogsignal travelling along optical cable to the receiver.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Local Area NetworksCablesEquipment AcquisitionTwisted PairCoaxial CablesFiber OpticsTutorialHardware Selection.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>